#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn51.10"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn51.10:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 51 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 51 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn51.10:0.2"
msgid "1. Cāpālavagga "
msgstr "1. At the Cāpāla Shrine "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn51.10:0.3"
msgid "10. Cetiyasutta "
msgstr "10. At the Cāpāla Shrine "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: pts-pi-vp5.259, sc1
msgctxt "sn51.10:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "sn51.10:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the hall with the peaked roof. "

msgctxt "sn51.10:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya vesāliṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Vesālī for alms. "

msgctxt "sn51.10:1.4"
msgid "Vesāliyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then, after the meal, on his return from alms-round, he addressed Venerable Ānanda: "

msgctxt "sn51.10:1.5"
msgid "“gaṇhāhi, ānanda, nisīdanaṃ. "
msgstr "“Ānanda, get your sitting cloth. "

#. VAR: cāpālaṃ cetiyaṃ → pāvālacetiyaṃ (s1-3, km) | cāpālacetiyaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "sn51.10:1.6"
msgid "Yena cāpālaṃ cetiyaṃ tenupasaṅkamissāma divāvihārāyā”ti. "
msgstr "Let’s go to the Cāpāla shrine for the day’s meditation.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn51.10:1.7"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paṭissutvā nisīdanaṃ ādāya bhagavantaṃ piṭṭhito piṭṭhito anubandhi. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” replied Ānanda. Taking his sitting cloth he followed behind the Buddha. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn51.10:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā yena cāpālaṃ cetiyaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha went up to the Cāpāla shrine, and sat down on the seat spread out. "

msgctxt "sn51.10:2.2"
msgid "Āyasmāpi kho ānando bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. "
msgstr "Ānanda bowed to the Buddha and sat down to one side. "

msgctxt "sn51.10:2.3"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
#. VAR: bahuputtaṃ cetiyaṃ → bahuputtakacetiyaṃ (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
#. VAR: sārandadaṃ cetiyaṃ → sārandadacetiyaṃ (s1-3) | ānandacetiyaṃ (mr) | sānandaraṃ (katthaci)
msgctxt "sn51.10:3.1"
msgid "“Ramaṇīyā, ānanda, vesālī, ramaṇīyaṃ udenaṃ cetiyaṃ, ramaṇīyaṃ gotamakaṃ cetiyaṃ, ramaṇīyaṃ sattambaṃ cetiyaṃ, ramaṇīyaṃ bahuputtaṃ cetiyaṃ, ramaṇīyaṃ sārandadaṃ cetiyaṃ, ramaṇīyaṃ cāpālaṃ cetiyaṃ. "
msgstr "“Ānanda, Vesālī is lovely. And the Udena, Gotamaka, Sattamba, Bahuputta, Sārandada, and Cāpāla shrines are all lovely. "

msgctxt "sn51.10:3.2"
msgid "Yassa kassaci, ānanda, cattāro iddhipādā bhāvitā bahulīkatā yānīkatā vatthukatā anuṭṭhitā paricitā susamāraddhā, so ākaṅkhamāno kappaṃ vā tiṭṭheyya kappāvasesaṃ vā. "
msgstr "Whoever has developed and cultivated the four bases of psychic power—made them a vehicle and a basis, kept them up, consolidated them, and properly implemented them—may, if they wish, live on for the eon or what’s left of the eon. "

msgctxt "sn51.10:3.3"
msgid "Tathāgatassa kho, ānanda, cattāro iddhipādā bhāvitā bahulīkatā yānīkatā vatthukatā anuṭṭhitā paricitā susamāraddhā. Ākaṅkhamāno, ānanda, tathāgato kappaṃ vā tiṭṭheyya kappāvasesaṃ vā”ti. "
msgstr "The Realized One has developed and cultivated the four bases of psychic power, made them a vehicle and a basis, kept them up, consolidated them, and properly implemented them. If he wished, the Realized One could live on for the eon or what’s left of the eon.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn51.10:4.1"
msgid "Evampi kho āyasmā ānando bhagavatā oḷārike nimitte kayiramāne oḷārike obhāse kayiramāne nāsakkhi paṭivijjhituṃ; "
msgstr "But Ānanda didn’t get it, even though the Buddha dropped such an obvious hint, such a clear sign. "

msgctxt "sn51.10:4.2"
msgid "na bhagavantaṃ yāci: "
msgstr "He didn’t beg the Buddha, "

#. VAR: sugato kappaṃ → sugato kappāvasesaṃ (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn51.10:4.3"
msgid "“tiṭṭhatu, bhante, bhagavā kappaṃ, tiṭṭhatu sugato kappaṃ bahujanahitāya bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānan”ti yathā taṃ mārena pariyuṭṭhitacitto. "
msgstr "“Sir, may the Blessed One please remain for the eon! May the Holy One please remain for the eon! That would be for the welfare and happiness of the people, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans.” For his mind was as if possessed by Māra. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.260, sc5
msgctxt "sn51.10:5.1"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho bhagavā … pe … "
msgstr "For a second time … "

msgctxt "sn51.10:5.2"
msgid "tatiyampi kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "and for a third time, the Buddha said to Ānanda: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn51.10:5.3"
msgid "“ramaṇīyā, ānanda, vesālī, ramaṇīyaṃ udenaṃ cetiyaṃ, ramaṇīyaṃ gotamakaṃ cetiyaṃ, ramaṇīyaṃ sattambaṃ cetiyaṃ, ramaṇīyaṃ bahuputtaṃ cetiyaṃ, ramaṇīyaṃ sārandadaṃ cetiyaṃ, ramaṇīyaṃ cāpālaṃ cetiyaṃ. "
msgstr "“Ānanda, Vesālī is lovely. And the Udena, Gotamaka, Sattamba, Bahuputta, Sārandada, and Cāpāla shrines are all lovely. "

msgctxt "sn51.10:5.4"
msgid "Yassa kassaci, ānanda, cattāro iddhipādā bhāvitā bahulīkatā yānīkatā vatthukatā anuṭṭhitā paricitā susamāraddhā, so ākaṅkhamāno kappaṃ vā tiṭṭheyya kappāvasesaṃ vā. "
msgstr "Whoever has developed and cultivated the four bases of psychic power—made them a vehicle and a basis, kept them up, consolidated them, and properly implemented them—may, if they wish, live on for the eon or what’s left of the eon. "

msgctxt "sn51.10:5.5"
msgid "Tathāgatassa kho, ānanda, cattāro iddhipādā bhāvitā bahulīkatā yānīkatā vatthukatā anuṭṭhitā paricitā susamāraddhā. Ākaṅkhamāno, ānanda, tathāgato kappaṃ vā tiṭṭheyya kappāvasesaṃ vā”ti. "
msgstr "The Realized One has developed and cultivated the four bases of psychic power, made them a vehicle and a basis, kept them up, consolidated them, and properly implemented them. If he wished, the Realized One could live on for the eon or what’s left of the eon.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn51.10:6.1"
msgid "Evampi kho āyasmā ānando bhagavatā oḷārike nimitte kayiramāne oḷārike obhāse kayiramāne nāsakkhi paṭivijjhituṃ; "
msgstr "But Ānanda didn’t get it, even though the Buddha dropped such an obvious hint, such a clear sign. "

msgctxt "sn51.10:6.2"
msgid "na bhagavantaṃ yāci: "
msgstr "He didn’t beg the Buddha, "

msgctxt "sn51.10:6.3"
msgid "“tiṭṭhatu, bhante, bhagavā kappaṃ, tiṭṭhatu sugato kappaṃ bahujanahitāya bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānan”ti yathā taṃ mārena pariyuṭṭhitacitto. "
msgstr "“Sir, may the Blessed One please remain for the eon! May the Holy One please remain for the eon! That would be for the welfare and happiness of the people, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans.” For his mind was as if possessed by Māra. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn51.10:7.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to him, "

msgctxt "sn51.10:7.2"
msgid "“gaccha kho tvaṃ, ānanda, "
msgstr "“Go now, Ānanda, "

msgctxt "sn51.10:7.3"
msgid "yassadāni kālaṃ maññasī”ti. "
msgstr "at your convenience.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn51.10:7.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paṭissutvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā avidūre aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle nisīdi. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” replied Ānanda. He rose from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before sitting at the root of a tree close by. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn51.10:8.1"
msgid "Atha kho māro pāpimā, acirapakkante āyasmante ānande, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "And then, not long after Ānanda had left, Māra the Wicked went up to the the Buddha and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.261, sc9
#. VAR: parinibbātu dāni sugato → parinibbātu sugato (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn51.10:9.1"
msgid "“Parinibbātu dāni, bhante, bhagavā, parinibbātu dāni sugato. Parinibbānakālo dāni, bhante, bhagavato. "
msgstr "“Sir, may the Blessed One now become fully extinguished! May the Holy One now become fully extinguished! Now is the time for the Buddha to become fully extinguished. "

msgctxt "sn51.10:9.2"
msgid "Bhāsitā kho panesā, bhante, bhagavatā vācā: "
msgstr "Sir, you once made this statement: "

#. VAR: uttānīkarissanti → uttanīkarissanti (pts1) | uttāniṃ karissanti (mr)
msgctxt "sn51.10:9.3"
msgid "‘na tāvāhaṃ, pāpima, parinibbāyissāmi yāva me bhikkhū na sāvakā bhavissanti viyattā vinītā visāradā bahussutā dhammadharā dhammānudhammappaṭipannā sāmīcippaṭipannā anudhammacārino, sakaṃ ācariyakaṃ uggahetvā ācikkhissanti desessanti paññapessanti paṭṭhapessanti vivarissanti vibhajissanti uttānīkarissanti, uppannaṃ parappavādaṃ sahadhammena suniggahitaṃ niggahetvā sappāṭihāriyaṃ dhammaṃ desessantī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Wicked One, I will not become fully extinguished until I have monk disciples who are competent, educated, assured, learned, have memorized the teachings, and practice in line with the teachings. Not until they practice properly, living in line with the teaching. Not until they’ve learned their teacher’s doctrine, and explain, teach, assert, establish, disclose, analyze, and make it clear. Not until they can legitimately and completely refute the doctrines of others that come up, and teach with a demonstrable basis.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "sn51.10:10.1"
msgid "Santi kho pana, bhante, etarahi bhikkhū bhagavato sāvakā viyattā vinītā visāradā bahussutā dhammadharā dhammānudhammappaṭipannā sāmīcippaṭipannā anudhammacārino, sakaṃ ācariyakaṃ uggahetvā ācikkhanti desenti paññapenti paṭṭhapenti vivaranti vibhajanti uttānīkaronti, uppannaṃ parappavādaṃ sahadhammena suniggahitaṃ niggahetvā sappāṭihāriyaṃ dhammaṃ desenti. "
msgstr "Today you do have such monk disciples. "

msgctxt "sn51.10:10.2"
msgid "Parinibbātu dāni, bhante, bhagavā, parinibbātu dāni, sugato. Parinibbānakālo dāni, bhante, bhagavato. "
msgstr "May the Blessed One now become fully extinguished! May the Holy One now become fully extinguished! Now is the time for the Buddha to become fully extinguished. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "sn51.10:11.1"
msgid "Bhāsitā kho panesā, bhante, bhagavatā vācā: "
msgstr "Sir, you once made this statement: "

msgctxt "sn51.10:11.2"
msgid "‘na tāvāhaṃ, pāpima, parinibbāyissāmi yāva me bhikkhuniyo na sāvikā bhavissanti viyattā vinītā visāradā bahussutā dhammadharā dhammānudhammappaṭipannā sāmīcippaṭipannā anudhammacāriniyo, sakaṃ ācariyakaṃ uggahetvā ācikkhissanti desessanti paññapessanti paṭṭhapessanti vivarissanti vibhajissanti uttānīkarissanti, uppannaṃ parappavādaṃ sahadhammena suniggahitaṃ niggahetvā sappāṭihāriyaṃ dhammaṃ desessantī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Wicked One, I will not become fully extinguished until I have nun disciples who are competent, educated, assured, learned …’ … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "sn51.10:12.1"
msgid "Santi kho pana, bhante, etarahi bhikkhuniyo bhagavato sāvikā viyattā vinītā visāradā bahussutā dhammadharā dhammānudhammappaṭipannā sāmīcippaṭipannā anudhammacāriniyo, sakaṃ ācariyakaṃ uggahetvā ācikkhanti desenti paññapenti paṭṭhapenti vivaranti vibhajanti uttānīkaronti, uppannaṃ parappavādaṃ sahadhammena suniggahitaṃ niggahetvā sappāṭihāriyaṃ dhammaṃ desenti. "
msgstr "Today you do have such nun disciples. "

msgctxt "sn51.10:12.2"
msgid "Parinibbātu dāni, bhante, bhagavā, parinibbātu dāni, sugato. Parinibbānakālo dāni, bhante, bhagavato. "
msgstr "May the Blessed One now become fully extinguished! May the Holy One now become fully extinguished! Now is the time for the Buddha to become fully extinguished. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "sn51.10:13.1"
msgid "Bhāsitā kho panesā, bhante, bhagavatā vācā: "
msgstr "Sir, you once made this statement: "

msgctxt "sn51.10:13.2"
msgid "‘na tāvāhaṃ, pāpima, parinibbāyissāmi yāva me upāsakā … pe … "
msgstr "‘Wicked One, I will not become fully extinguished until I have layman disciples … "

msgctxt "sn51.10:13.3"
msgid "yāva me upāsikā na sāvikā bhavissanti viyattā vinītā visāradā bahussutā dhammadharā dhammānudhammappaṭipannā sāmīcippaṭipannā anudhammacāriniyo, sakaṃ ācariyakaṃ uggahetvā ācikkhissanti desessanti paññapessanti paṭṭhapessanti vivarissanti vibhajissanti uttānīkarissanti, uppannaṃ parappavādaṃ sahadhammena suniggahitaṃ niggahetvā sappāṭihāriyaṃ dhammaṃ desessantī’ti. "
msgstr "and laywoman disciples who are competent, educated, assured, learned …’ … "

# NOTE: Note the mixing up of the gender sequence, not found in AN 8.70 or DN 16.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.262, sc14
msgctxt "sn51.10:14.1"
msgid "Santi kho pana, bhante, etarahi upāsakā … "
msgstr "Today you do have such layman "

msgctxt "sn51.10:14.2"
msgid "upāsikā bhagavato sāvikā viyattā vinītā visāradā bahussutā dhammadharā dhammānudhammappaṭipannā sāmīcippaṭipannā anudhammacāriniyo, sakaṃ ācariyakaṃ uggahetvā ācikkhanti desenti paññapenti paṭṭhapenti vivaranti vibhajanti uttānīkaronti, uppannaṃ parappavādaṃ sahadhammena suniggahitaṃ niggahetvā sappāṭihāriyaṃ dhammaṃ desenti. "
msgstr "and laywoman disciples. "

msgctxt "sn51.10:14.3"
msgid "Parinibbātu dāni, bhante, bhagavā, parinibbātu dāni, sugato. Parinibbānakālo dāni, bhante, bhagavato. "
msgstr "May the Blessed One now become fully extinguished! May the Holy One now become fully extinguished! Now is the time for the Buddha to become fully extinguished. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "sn51.10:15.1"
msgid "Bhāsitā kho panesā, bhante, bhagavatā vācā: "
msgstr "Sir, you once made this statement: "

msgctxt "sn51.10:15.2"
msgid "‘na tāvāhaṃ, pāpima, parinibbāyissāmi yāva me idaṃ brahmacariyaṃ na iddhañceva bhavissati phītañca vitthāritaṃ bāhujaññaṃ puthubhūtaṃ yāva devamanussehi suppakāsitan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Wicked One, I will not become fully extinguished until my spiritual life is successful and prosperous, extensive, popular, widespread, and well proclaimed wherever there are gods and humans.’ "

msgctxt "sn51.10:15.3"
msgid "Tayidaṃ, bhante, bhagavato brahmacariyaṃ iddhañceva phītañca vitthāritaṃ bāhujaññaṃ puthubhūtaṃ yāva devamanussehi suppakāsitaṃ. "
msgstr "Today your spiritual life is successful and prosperous, extensive, popular, widespread, and well proclaimed wherever there are gods and humans. "

msgctxt "sn51.10:15.4"
msgid "Parinibbātu dāni, bhante, bhagavā, parinibbātu dāni sugato. Parinibbānakālo dāni, bhante, bhagavato”ti. "
msgstr "May the Blessed One now become fully extinguished! May the Holy One now become fully extinguished! Now is the time for the Buddha to become fully extinguished.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "sn51.10:16.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā māraṃ pāpimantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When this was said, the Buddha said to Māra, "

#. VAR: Na ciraṃ → nacirasseva (mr)
msgctxt "sn51.10:16.2"
msgid "“appossukko tvaṃ, pāpima, hohi. Na ciraṃ tathāgatassa parinibbānaṃ bhavissati. "
msgstr "“Relax, Wicked One. The final extinguishment of the Realized One will be soon. "

msgctxt "sn51.10:16.3"
msgid "Ito tiṇṇaṃ māsānaṃ accayena tathāgato parinibbāyissatī”ti. "
msgstr "Three months from now the Realized One will finally be extinguished.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
#. VAR: ossaji → ossajji (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "sn51.10:17.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā cāpāle cetiye sato sampajāno āyusaṅkhāraṃ ossaji. "
msgstr "So at the Cāpāla tree shrine the Buddha, mindful and aware, surrendered the life force. "

#. VAR: Ossaṭṭhe ca → ossaṭṭhe pana (pts1) | osajje pana (mr)
#. VAR: devadundubhiyo → devadudrabhiyo (mr)
msgctxt "sn51.10:17.2"
msgid "Ossaṭṭhe ca bhagavatā āyusaṅkhāre mahābhūmicālo ahosi bhiṃsanako lomahaṃso, devadundubhiyo ca phaliṃsu. "
msgstr "When he did so there was a great earthquake, awe-inspiring and hair-raising, and thunder cracked the sky. "

msgctxt "sn51.10:17.3"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etamatthaṃ viditvā tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imaṃ udānaṃ udānesi: "
msgstr "Then, knowing the meaning of this, on that occasion the Buddha was inspired to exclaim: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.263, sc18
msgctxt "sn51.10:18.1"
msgid "“Tulamatulañca sambhavaṃ, "
msgstr "“Weighing up the incomparable against an extension of life, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn51.10:18.2"
msgid "Bhavasaṅkhāramavassaji muni; "
msgstr "the sage surrendered the life force. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn51.10:18.3"
msgid "Ajjhattarato samāhito, "
msgstr "Happy inside, serene, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn51.10:18.4"
msgid "Abhindi kavacamivattasambhavan”ti. "
msgstr "he burst out of this self-made chain like a suit of armor.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn51.10:18.5"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn51.10:18.6"
msgid "Cāpālavaggo paṭhamo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc19
msgctxt "sn51.10:19.1"
msgid "Apārāpi viraddho ca, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn51.10:19.2"
msgid "ariyā nibbidāpi ca; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn51.10:19.3"
msgid "Padesaṃ samattaṃ bhikkhu, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn51.10:19.4"
msgid "buddhaṃ ñāṇañca cetiyanti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
